def: One who shrinks; one who withdraws from danger.
One who conforms to or inculcates Judaism; specifically, pl.(Ch. Hist.), those Jews who accepted Christianity but still adheredto the law of Moses and worshiped in the temple at Jerusalem.
A little or young wolf. Tennyson.
The act of staying or residing in a place. [Obs.] Bp. Hall.
A genus of dipterous insects, including the gnat and mosquito.
Chewing the cud; characterized by chewing again what has beenswallowed; of or pertaining to the Ruminantia.
